a:5:{s:2:"id";s:8:"18678171";s:4:"info";a:4:{s:6:"Title:";s:21:"session_cookie_domain";s:7:"Author:";s:15:"Shaun McCormick";s:16:"Last Changed by:";s:15:"Shaun McCormick";s:12:"Wiki Markup:";s:36:"[revolution20:session_cookie_domain]";}s:6:"parent";s:8:"18678127";s:6:"source";s:753:"h2. session_cookie_domain

*Name*: Session Cookie Domain
*Type*: String
*Default*: localhost

Use this setting to customize the session cookie domain. 

{warning}You will need to clear your local cookies in your browser after changing this setting.{warning}

This setting is useful to change if you are running multiple Contexts on one top-level domain, but want to share logins across them. For example, changing the setting to:

{quote}.mydomain.com{quote}

will allow all MODX sessions to persist across any *.mydomain.com site, allowing logins to work across subdomains.

{note}This setting isn&#39;t in MODx by default, as it&#39;s best to let PHP calculate this on its own. Only set this if you are sure of what you are doing.{note}
\\
